CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1962, pg. 2 reads: "Talking It Over...are Wendell Freeland (left), William P. Young (center) and Republican gubernatorial candidate William W. Scranton, in the latter's suite at the Penn-Sheraton Hotel, Last Friday afternoon. They discussed the role of the Negro voter in the fall elections. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Wendell Freeland, William P. Young, and Republican gubernatorial candidate William "Bill" Scranton, seated in suite in Penn Sheraton
